[SN]TITLE[SN]
Blind drivers take to Castle Donington racetrack

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Dozens of blind and partially-sighted people have had the chance to take to the wheel of a car at a special event in the East Midlands.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
6 September 2015 Last updated at 12:04 BST
Some of the drivers have never been able to see, but others lost their sight through injury or illness.
The event at the Castle Donington racetrack raised money for the Guide Dogs for the Blind.
